post_text:
Andreas Aguirre posted in San Saba ISD

Correction to UIL physicals

San Saba has teamed up with Baylor Scott and White to offer physicals at a low rate. Physicals will be done by appointment only. When calling, please let them know it is for a UIL physical. Parents are required to attend physical examinations. Payment will be according to insurance coverage. There will be a $15 dollar charge for students who do not have insurance.

Students that must receive a physical:

-All in coming 7th grade students participating in any extracurricular activities.

-All 8th grade band members who have not gotten a physical in the past two years.

-Any athlete, band member, or cheerleader who hasn‚Äôt gotten a physical in the past 2 years.

-Any athlete that has received a concussion, broken bone, or hospital visit in the past year.

post_text:
During the school year San Saba High School sports teams and clubs will be looking for ways to fundraise. One popular method is by selling sponsorships in programs and school calendars, etc but unfortunately, con artists may capitalize on this school spirit.
At San Saba we encourage all of our Athletes and Clubs to communicate face to face with our local business and community members. We have once again been made aware of people calling and posing as members of a school organization. Please do not give out credit card or commit to purchase anything over the phone. Please continue to help support our Great Community and District but be diligent in making sure where your money is going.
Thank you San Saba ISD
Always a Great Day to be an Armadillo!
text:
During the school year San Saba High School sports teams and clubs will be looking for ways to fundraise. One popular method is by selling sponsorships in programs and school calendars, etc but unfortunately, con artists may capitalize on this school spirit.
At San Saba we encourage all of our Athletes and Clubs to communicate face to face with our local business and community members. We have once again been made aware of people calling and posing as members of a school organization. Please do not give out credit card or commit to purchase anything over the phone. Please continue to help support our Great Community and District but be diligent in making sure where your money is going.
Thank you San Saba ISD
Always a Great Day to be an Armadillo!

San Saba High School Student Council will host a drop-off station from 10am to 12pm on Monday, July 2nd in front of the George Dennis Science Building. People should be able to drive through and drop off donations or care packages for the two students that are in the hospital in Fort Worth.

The following young ladies received All-State honors for their great performances this track season. They were selected among the best in the state for the 2A classification. We are so proud of all their hard work and dedication.

L to R: Courtnee Cash, Kaleigh Ellis, Analyn Bohensky, Ashlynn Cash, and Brighton Adams.
text:
The following young ladies received All-State honors for their great performances this track season. They were selected among the best in the state for the 2A classification. We are so proud of all their hard work and dedication.
They have represented San Saba High School with pride and honor. Congratulations on these deserving awards!
L to R: Courtnee Cash, Kaleigh Ellis, Analyn Bohensky, Ashlynn Cash, and Brighton Adams.

post_text:
Kaleigh Ellis and Ashlynn Cash were selected as Texas Girls Coach Association Track All-Stars for their outstanding track season. They were two of only twenty four athletes selected from conferences 1A-4A. They will be participating in the track demonstration at the TGCA clinic on July 10th in Arlington.
Analyn Bohensky was selected to the Texas Girls Coaches Association Legacy team for Track and Field. The Legacy team honors senior athletes who have had outstanding track careers during their high school years. Analyn was a four-year state qualifier in the pole vault. Congratulations to these young ladies on these well deserved honors!
